HEADWORD: Tunicin
<hw>Tu"ni*cin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>Animal cellulose; a substance present in the mantle,
or tunic, of the Tunicates, which resembles, or is identical with, the
cellulose of the vegetable kingdom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

